[SHORT DESC]
Ignores evasion modifiers.

[LONG DESC]
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>Deals damage and ignores all accuracy and evasion modifiers.</p>

<h2>Competitive Use</h2>
<p>Faint Attack is for the most part outclassed by Crunch and Night Slash due to the existence of the Evasion Clause. It is stronger than both moves if the user's ability is Technician, however.</p>

<h2>Related Moves</h2>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/crunch">Crunch</a> is a more powerful option, with the chance to lower the opponent's Defense.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/night_slash">Night Slash</a> is more powerful and has an increased chance to land a critical hit.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/aerial_ace">Aerial Ace</a> is a Flying-type equivalent.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/shadow_punch">Shadow Punch</a> is a Ghost-type equivalent.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/magnet_bomb">Magnet Bomb</a> is a Steel-type equivalent.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/magical_leaf">Magical Leaf</a> is a special Grass-type equivalent.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/shock_wave">Shock Wave</a> is a special Electric-type equivalent.</p>